00:31:09.870 --> 00:31:14.150
"In the years before her death,

00:31:14.150 --> 00:31:18.290
my maternal grandmother told me
the story of her family's flight

00:31:18.290 --> 00:31:21.930
from Shreveport to
Summerville, Louisiana.

00:31:21.930 --> 00:31:26.250
My great-grandfather who
owned his own sheet metal shop

00:31:26.250 --> 00:31:31.730
in that left behind town who
could read and write and figure

00:31:31.730 --> 00:31:36.730
and who understood his worth,
entered his business one morning

00:31:36.730 --> 00:31:40.820
and found his young
cousin dead on a worktable.

00:31:40.820 --> 00:31:45.290
A note pinned to the body warned
my great-grandfather to get

00:31:45.290 --> 00:31:52.130
out of town before nightfall,
but less he be killed as well.

00:31:52.130 --> 00:31:55.320
The surviving family piled
into a wagon with nothing

00:31:55.320 --> 00:31:57.670
but what the wagon could hold.

00:31:57.670 --> 00:32:01.070
'Imagine that', my
grandmother said repeatedly

00:32:01.070 --> 00:32:03.920
in the last years of her life.

00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:07.110
She didn't talk much about
the new shop or the new town

00:32:07.110 --> 00:32:09.260
and the years before
she died it was

00:32:09.260 --> 00:32:11.530
that wagon my grandmother
talked about,

00:32:11.530 --> 00:32:18.080
loaded with things her family
could haul and that life plucked

00:32:18.080 --> 00:32:20.830
from her family's line.

00:32:20.830 --> 00:32:24.290
Most Black American
families have a story

00:32:24.290 --> 00:32:29.420
of some branch brutally
severed from their family tree.

00:32:29.420 --> 00:32:32.070
The only remarkable thing
about my grandmother's story is

00:32:32.070 --> 00:32:35.380
that she had to reach
as far back as 1917

00:32:35.380 --> 00:32:37.510
to encounter such a trauma.

00:32:37.510 --> 00:32:40.310
But pain is an immortal humor,

00:32:40.310 --> 00:32:44.510
lasting in a body far
longer than pleasure.

00:32:44.510 --> 00:32:47.030
Again, and again my
grandmother asked me

00:32:47.030 --> 00:32:51.960
as if I might one visit provide
some satisfactory answer,

00:32:51.960 --> 00:32:56.300
what would make a
person do that to a body?

00:32:56.300 --> 00:32:59.650
We might be playing with the
baby, grandmother's namesake.

00:32:59.650 --> 00:33:03.270
We might be sitting in a nursing
home's courtyard enjoying the

00:33:03.270 --> 00:33:06.050
light of the springtime sun.

00:33:06.050 --> 00:33:09.450
Once we in a communal
dining room surrounded

00:33:09.450 --> 00:33:11.750
by the dying old White Iowans

00:33:11.750 --> 00:33:15.640
with whom my grandparents
spent their final years.

00:33:15.640 --> 00:33:19.510
She looked around if startled to
find herself amongst strangers

00:33:19.510 --> 00:33:22.750
and whispered the story
of her family's flight

00:33:22.750 --> 00:33:26.100
as if it were a story
that I that moment

00:33:26.100 --> 00:33:30.930
for my very survival
needed to hear.

00:33:30.930 --> 00:33:34.620
Grandmother's voice shook
when she recited this story,

00:33:34.620 --> 00:33:38.630
not from age, but from the
hard-driven grief that spoke

00:33:38.630 --> 00:33:42.720
through muscle to bone,
this must be what they mean

00:33:42.720 --> 00:33:45.410
by this role of terror.

00:33:45.410 --> 00:33:47.970
My grandmother repeated
her story,

00:33:47.970 --> 00:33:50.910
because she could not
help but remember.

00:33:50.910 --> 00:33:52.420
She was there.

00:33:52.420 --> 00:33:55.170
She walked into the
shop and saw her cousin.

00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:58.380
She climbed into the wagon
and rode through the dust.

00:33:58.380 --> 00:34:03.210
She felt her father's
fear-born defiance and caution.

00:34:03.210 --> 00:34:07.020
She saw her pregnant mother,
several siblings packed up

00:34:07.020 --> 00:34:09.990
and driven off before
the last of the light.

00:34:09.990 --> 00:34:14.820
She was there you understand
and she had to tell me.

00:34:14.820 --> 00:34:18.350
Though, she would likely have
been too young at the time

00:34:18.350 --> 00:34:22.590
to remember the incident,
this too is possible.

00:34:22.590 --> 00:34:27.740
Hers was the small body
inside her mother's body.

00:34:27.740 --> 00:34:32.360
She might not yet have
even been conceived.

00:34:32.360 --> 00:34:36.780
This is how history
eclipses all reality.

00:34:36.780 --> 00:34:41.990
My grandmother, who could not
help but relive this trauma,

00:34:41.990 --> 00:34:44.700
was also as far away

00:34:44.700 --> 00:34:50.560
from everything I am
writing as you and as me."

