00:37:04.450 --> 00:37:07.820
"In childhood she had laid
awake at night on fire

00:37:07.820 --> 00:37:12.500
with a single question; 'How
did French people know what they

00:37:12.500 --> 00:37:13.920
were saying?'

00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:17.660
You know, when she
finally asked her mother,

00:37:17.660 --> 00:37:19.140
she didn't know either

00:37:19.140 --> 00:37:23.200
which meant the problem
must be inherited.

00:37:23.200 --> 00:37:26.100
'Can't learn', she
Googled late at night.

00:37:26.100 --> 00:37:29.670
Can't learn since
losing my virginity?

00:37:29.670 --> 00:37:31.830
Her most secret pleasures
were sentences

00:37:31.830 --> 00:37:35.060
that only half the percent of
people on earth would understand

00:37:35.060 --> 00:37:38.910
and that no one would be able
to decipher it all in ten years.

00:37:38.910 --> 00:37:41.410
Grizzly British witch pits,

00:37:41.410 --> 00:37:45.730
sex in the moon next
summer, what is binged?

00:37:45.730 --> 00:37:47.950
What is to be corncobbed?

00:37:47.950 --> 00:37:53.380
That's the cost of my vegan
lunch, pan [inaudible] my wound.

00:37:53.380 --> 00:37:55.820
She could not feel
her first fingertip.

00:37:55.820 --> 00:37:59.100
This in the way that your ear
used to get soft pink compliant

00:37:59.100 --> 00:38:02.260
and the swirls of hair
around it like damp designs

00:38:02.260 --> 00:38:04.820
from talking on the telephone.

00:38:04.820 --> 00:38:07.810
A hundred years ago her cat
might have been called 'Mittens'

00:38:07.810 --> 00:38:09.670
or 'Pussy willow.'

00:38:09.670 --> 00:38:13.510
Now her cat was called
'Dr. Butthole.'

00:38:13.510 --> 00:38:15.020
There was no way out of it.

00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:18.820
'Dr. Butthole' she called
at night almost in despair

00:38:18.820 --> 00:38:21.220
until he trotted to the door
with the bright feathers

00:38:21.220 --> 00:38:24.050
of her dignity clinging to
his lips and disappeared

00:38:24.050 --> 00:38:27.500
in his alternating
stripes over the threshold.

00:38:27.500 --> 00:38:31.240
In Bristol the sunset dripped
as if from a honeycomb.

00:38:31.240 --> 00:38:33.680
'This is your contribution
to society?'

00:38:33.680 --> 00:38:35.810
a man asked holding up a print

00:38:35.810 --> 00:38:41.510
out of her most famous
post, 'Can a dog be twins?'

00:38:41.510 --> 00:38:45.860
[ Laughter ]

00:38:45.860 --> 00:38:47.890
'Yes', Rachel peeped.

00:38:47.890 --> 00:38:50.280
She wanted to explain that she
had also popularized the concept

00:38:50.280 --> 00:38:53.770
of today's ceiling wax
manicure where you paint it

00:38:53.770 --> 00:38:57.360
over your entire fingertip
in a big careless red blob

00:38:57.360 --> 00:39:01.080
and that this had paved
the way for 1776 Corp,

00:39:01.080 --> 00:39:02.480
an irony-based esthetic

00:39:02.480 --> 00:39:04.600
where people adopted
various visual signifiers

00:39:04.600 --> 00:39:07.200
to the founding fathers, but
he had already turned away

00:39:07.200 --> 00:39:12.620
in disgust tearing the print up
in two as he went, just as well.

00:39:12.620 --> 00:39:16.630
It probably wouldn't be funny
to an Englishman anyway.

00:39:16.630 --> 00:39:19.790
But afterward, a boyish figure
stood in line to see her.

00:39:19.790 --> 00:39:21.090
He waited until the very end.

00:39:21.090 --> 00:39:24.990
'I used to read your
online diary' he confessed

00:39:24.990 --> 00:39:27.670
when it was finally his
turn and tears sparked

00:39:27.670 --> 00:39:30.040
in her eyes instantaneously.

00:39:30.040 --> 00:39:33.090
The diary she had written before
anything had happened to her.

00:39:33.090 --> 00:39:34.750
