could put together

01:06:00.870 --> 01:06:03.870
that supposedly don't
belong together.

01:06:03.870 --> 01:06:09.110
And so, I think that having
genres is helpful in a way

01:06:09.110 --> 01:06:10.930
because it helps
us both as writers

01:06:10.930 --> 01:06:14.620
and readers approach the work
with kinds of expectations,

01:06:14.620 --> 01:06:16.680
but when we're composing,

01:06:16.680 --> 01:06:21.480
I imagine that those
things become less useful

01:06:21.480 --> 01:06:23.480
or they're only useful
in that we're trying

01:06:23.480 --> 01:06:27.300
to breakdown those
very rigid categories.

01:06:27.300 --> 01:06:28.600
&gt;&gt; Patricia Lockwood: I think

01:06:28.600 --> 01:06:30.730
if there's one thing the good
