01:06:30.730 --> 01:06:33.170
that good poetry has to have
I think a good prose doesn't

01:06:33.170 --> 01:06:37.160
necessarily, and I think that
good poetry has to make a leap

01:06:37.160 --> 01:06:38.460
through the air of the minds.

01:06:38.460 --> 01:06:41.170
I mean you can write a novel
where that doesn't ever happen,

01:06:41.170 --> 01:06:43.190
but I think in all good
poems there is a moment

01:06:43.190 --> 01:06:46.020
where you just fly and we
know what that moment is,

01:06:46.020 --> 01:06:49.240
like you feel it, you feel
something almost like pass

01:06:49.240 --> 01:06:51.640
through the ether in your
brain, it's a connection,

01:06:51.640 --> 01:06:53.110
but it's like above
the connection.

01:06:53.110 --> 01:06:55.660
And you don't necessarily need
to have that in a narrative.

01:06:55.660 --> 01:06:58.210
So, I guess that's how I
identify those like kind

01:06:58.210 --> 01:07:00.310
